      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@fanquake Great suggestions, thanks. Will incorporate them all shortly. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> Somewhat unrelated, but after this change, how often are we using the\r\n> \r\n> ```c++\r\n> #ifdef WIN32\r\n>     if (strerror_s(...\r\n> ```\r\n> \r\n> case in `SysErrorString`? Wondering if we can (in general) further consolidate this error logging.\r\n\r\nI don't think in many places. In addition to the potential use of it for `fflush` in this PR, there's this:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/3eaf7be6ade22c99f3c0000122e49b94de868d74/src/init.cpp#L164\r\n\r\nIf I artificially trigger that using the current code (by giving it an impossible path), it shows:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"250\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116917595/206523440-32d8edca-54b2-4974-851f-d0077ffae27d.png\">\r\n\r\nIf I substitute it with `Win32ErrorString(GetLastError())`, I get:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"250\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116917595/206524042-ede807f2-c588-4bc3-8415-5d5e943af95d.png\">\r\n\r\nSince the error codes are [unrelated](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/20056851/getlasterror-errno-formatmessagea-and-strerror-s#comment29875130_20056851) (`errno` and `GetLastError()` return different actual values), I think it'd be difficult to consolidate effectively.\r\n\r\nPotentially, we could have a `std::string GetSystemErrorReason()` function that called `SysErrorString(errno)` on non-Win32 and `Win32ErrorString(GetLastError())` on Win32, but I'm not certain that (on Win32) _every time_ `errno` is set that `GetLastError()` is also set. ",
      "created_at" : "2022-12-08T18:24:50Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/26654#issuecomment-1343146227",
